title: note-lisa-and-mac
summary: Apple Lisa (1983) and Macintosh (1984) — first commercial computers with a graphical interface and mouse to reach a wide audience
tags: HistoryOfComputing

The Lisa ($9,995 in 1983) was too expensive to succeed commercially but proved the concept. The Macintosh (January 1984, $2,495) was designed by Jobs to be affordable. It shipped with MacPaint and MacWrite, applications that demonstrated to ordinary people what a GUI could do. The 1984 Super Bowl advertisement, directed by Ridley Scott, is still studied in marketing courses. The Mac's influence on the PC industry culminated in Windows 95, which adopted the taskbar/desktop model that has persisted ever since.
